Reasoning: The paper deals with the generalization of the restricted isometry constant (RIC) in compressive sensing (CS) to restricted isometry random variable (RIV) and its probability distributions, RIC prediction, and phase transition analysis for Gaussian encoders. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
